				<title>Staff Post - Tag Reversion (Open)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2244191/scp-2823#post-2806766</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 01 May 2017 02:43:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MrWrong</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2039383</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Noting that I have deleted a tag 'euclid' made by BlushingPossum. Please note that if one wants to tag, they should tag the article entirely and not just one or two.</p> <p>Staff can assist in tagging articles. However, untagged articles are usually identified for tagging and staff will have a harder time to find incorrectly-tagged articles.</p> <p>Ergo, if you do not know all the necessary parts when tagging articles, do not tag.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
